	(text "According to the calculation from our engineers:\n•	For Single Ended 40ohm in L1 and L10, the trace width should be maintained at 7.26mil.\n•	For Single Ended 40ohm in L3/L5/L7 , the trace width should be 6.09mil.\n•	For Single Ended 50ohm L1/L10 , the trace width should be 4.5mil.\n•	For Single Ended 50Ohm in L5, L7 the trace width should be 4mil.\n\n•	For Differential Pair 80ohm (80Z_DIFF) in L3/L5 , the trace width and spacing should be 5.25mil and 5.12mil respectively.\n•	For Differential Pair in L1 (to be updated), the trace width and spacing should be 5.42mil and 5.32mil respectively.\n•	For Differential Pair in L1 (to be updated), the trace width and spacing should be 5.66mil and 6.11mil respectively.\n•	For Differential Pair 100ohm (100Z_DIFF) in L1/L10 , the trace width and spacing should be 4.2mil and 13.98mil respectively.\n"
